to the editor edmund morgan op ed dec 31 says benjamin franklin 's list of virtues was an act of rebellion against the religious definition of virtue that prevailed at the time in fact all of franklin 's 13 virtues are rooted in biblical values or religious thought the book of wisdom celebrates justice as the fount of all morality the catholic spiritual tradition includes temperance among its cardinal virtues augustine exalts silence as essential to transcendence aquinas ranks moderation next to prudence and the old and new testaments place their highest value on humility and so it is with all of franklin 's virtues they are moral injunctions deeply rooted in our religious traditions one is tempted to say that they are the best guides we have to moral perfection in a morally imperfect world donald p kommers notre dame ind jan 1 2003

